CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F407A1772539377
OL,3,CMan charged with criminal damage after
OL,4,CChurchill statue defaced with graffiti
OL,6,FOn Friday, a Greater London Authority
OL,7,Fspokesperson said: "We are appalled by
OL,8,Fthis vandalism to the statue of Sir
OL,9,FWinston Churchill and work is under
OL,10,Fway to remove the graffiti as quickly
OL,11,Fas possible."
OL,13,FDowning Street also commented on the
OL,14,Fvandalism of the statue, labelling it
OL,15,F"completely abhorrent".
OL,17,FA Number 10 spokesman said: "Churchill
OL,18,Fwas a great Briton. This Government
OL,19,Fwill always stand up for our values
OL,20,Fand the perpetrator must be held to
OL,21,Faccount."
